node.text: Until just recently, Vancouver Island’s landmass was almost entirely old-growth rainforest, yet only about 10% remains today thanks to industrial logging. These old trees play a critical role in boosting a forest’s immunity – when we lose them, we lose the blueprint of an entire ecosystem’s resilience. We cannot level what took hundreds, even thousands, of years for nature to perfect and expect it ever to recover, so we need your help. Governments and large corporations feel secure making harmful environmental decisions when allowed to operate in the shadows, often taking special measures to prevent the public from becoming aware of their actions. Well, we can see them now, and we are not about to let them get away with it. Please visit the link in my bio and urge BC officials to protect the last of our old-growth forests before it is too late. Video by @ReelWater. node.text: 🔊 Please turn up your volume to learn about Timor-Leste's incredible marine ecosystems and get a behind-the-scenes look at our encounter with a magnificent blue whale. Looking into the eye of the largest animal that has ever lived on our planet and seeing them stare back was an experience that changed me forever. I have been fortunate enough to visit many unique locations, and I have seen some wonderful things in my career, but there are only a handful of memories I'll think about on my deathbed. This is one of them. The cobalt waters of Timor-Leste are abundant with an incredible variety of life, making responsible, sustainable ecotourism an ideal way for local communities to support themselves. Our objective at @sealegacy and @onlyone is to share the beauty and wonder of these faraway places so people everywhere will be inspired to stand up and protect them from the threat of climate change and other human-made issues. Please consider visiting the link in my bio and supporting our conservation mission by joining The Tide today. On expedition for @sealegacy in Timor-Leste with @mitty, @andy_mann, and @sonyalpha. #ShotOnSony #SonyAlpha #BeAlpha #whale #bluewhale #timorleste #life #beauty #conservation #bucketlist

node.text: There’s only one thing in wildlife and nature photography that really matters, and that’s the moment. Every situation that unfolds in front of me is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to tell a story that can connect a global audience to the most important issues facing our planet. There is always more than just my creative vision to consider, especially underwater – am I weighted properly, is everything working, where are the other divers, where are the other sharks. But if I can shoot 8K video and 50 MP stills with the same tool, I have one less thing to worry about and am free to go off and be an artist. Conservation and storytelling are my passions – it is a pleasure to have partners that make it easier to succeed. node.text: The Galápagos is an invaluable and irreplaceable treasure of our ocean – a truly legendary World Heritage Site that is a refuge for 3,000 marine species. Yet, industrial and unsustainable fishing practices continue to plunder its waters and devastate its fragile ecosystem thanks to inaction from a government that has pledged to protect it. Please visit the link in my bio where you can show your support for additional protections by signing our petition – we need your help to ensure Ecuadorian President @leninmorenog and President of the National Assembly @cesarlitardo fulfill their commitment to expanding the Galápagos Marine Reserve before any further damage is done. With @onlyone and @sealegacy. @mas_galapagos2020 #masgalapagos #yoestoycongalapagos #galapagos #ecuador #gratitude

node.text: Today is @mitty's birthday. I am so fortunate and thankful to have a partner in life who not only matches my passion but magnifies it. Cristina is a caring mother, talented diver, fearless explorer, gifted photographer, and tireless conservationist. She is wise and kind, and leads with a gentle heart. She makes everyone around her better, myself included. Please consider celebrating her birthday with me by visiting the link in my bio and joining The Tide to support our conservation mission at @sealegacy and our activation platform, @onlyone – 100% of your contribution will go directly to projects and campaigns to rebuild marine life. As always, thank you for standing with us to protect the world's oceans – your support means the world to all of us. Feel free to leave a birthday message for her below, and I'll be sure she sees them. #onlyoneocean #birthday #partner #inspiration #luckyguy

node.text: The fjords of northern Norway are unlike any place on Earth. I have visited several times during my career and captured many of my proudest images there. Now, talk of seismic oil and gas exploration threatens to put Lofoten's enormous orca population at risk. I am excited to announce the upcoming @onlyone screening of our new short documentary film, 'Echoes in the Arctic,' on Tuesday, November 10th, at 7 pm ET (4 pm PT). Filmmakers @mitty, @andymaser, @tahriasheather, and I will be sticking around afterward for a live Q&A, so be sure to RSVP at the link in my bio – hope to see you there. #onlyoneocean #orca #lofoten #norway #documentary #filmmaking #climatechange #conservation #storytelling

node.text: 🔊 // Art and storytelling have sparked many beautiful relationships in my career, but few are as meaningful as this one. I have spent countless evenings sifting through my image library with @thelumineers blasting in the background, so to discover that @jeremiahfraites, co-founder of my favourite band, had one of my fine art pieces hanging on his wall was a wonderful surprise. Soon after connecting, I discovered we had much more in common than a healthy appreciation for each other's art. Jeremiah and his wife, @francesca_laz, are avid conservationists who care deeply about the same bears in Katmai, Alaska, that I have been obsessed with ever since photographing them in 1991, long before my @natgeo days. He recently sent me a demo of "Maggie" after divulging his upcoming solo project, and I instantly recognized it as an opportunity to collaborate. Today, I am proud to share the music video we crafted together. Most of this footage has never been seen outside the @sealegacy walls – it is a tribute to the intelligent, majestic, and vulnerable brown bears of Alaska. Together, we hope our art will inspire you to join us in a stand against the Pebble Mine development that threatens to wipe out their habitat. The time for action is now – visit the link in my bio to send a message to Senator Sullivan, Senator Murkowski, and the EPA today. Filmed on assignment for @sealegacy with @andymaser, @samkretch, and @kyle.roepke. #jeremiahfraites #thelumineers #maggie #pianopiano #newmusic #bear #brownbear #katmai #bristolbay #alaska #pebblemine #stoppebblemine #vetopebblemine #nopebblemine #shareyourbears #thinkaboutbears #art #collaboration #conservation #passion

node.text: 🔊 Please turn up your volume and come on a journey with me to witness the remarkable coastal wolves of British Columbia. // I am really proud of our small but mighty @sealegacy team when I see them create powerful and impactful storytelling pieces. Please watch the entire film and let me know your thoughts. @sealegacy and our partners at @raincoastconservation have a plan to end the commercial trophy hunting of wolves, bears, and wolverines in British Columbia’s Kitlope Conservancy permanently, but we need your help. Two very generous patrons have just confirmed they will donation-match half of the final $100,000 needed to buy up the remaining hunting licenses in the area, which would double the impact of your contribution. A good friend of mine and avid supporter of @sealegacy just came in for $20K. Please visit the link in my bio if you want to get involved in pushing this protection over the finish line so we can save this community of wolves. 🙏💙 Shot on assignment for @sealegacy with @johnkelseyphoto. Audio and BTS clips by @maxwelhohn, @steve_woods_photography, and @seaforthexpeditions. node.text: 🔊 Sound on to hear @mitty tell the beautiful story of the Mermaids of Atauro – I couldn't resist lifting it from her account to share with all of you. I am always in awe of how easily she connects with people on expedition. Her energy is infectious, kind, and gentle – people invite her into their worlds the same way animals let me into theirs. It helps that she speaks several languages, Portuguese in this case. Next month, we board our boat and set off on assignment with the @sealegacy team to unearth more moments like this. In the meantime, click my bio link to sign up for @onlyone and watch more from "The Last Coral Kingdom" series on our 30x30 journey. // Reposted from @mitty: "'Obrigada pela natureza.' The song drifted across the sea from a woman moving waist-deep in the shallows of Timor-Leste, her voice rising gently with the rolling swells. I knew instantly who she was and waded out to her from shore, tears welling in my eyes as I recognized the meaning behind the Portuguese words. Spanning around her in a wide circle were a handful of tiny boats trailing baited hooks through the water, an ingenious fishing technique I had never seen before used by the Wawata Tapu; the Mermaids of Auturo. As I drew close, she smiled brightly and sang again, "Obrigada pela natureza, hallelujah!" A fisherwoman's hymn giving thanks to nature for providing for her family. A surge of hope flooded through me, and in that moment, I wanted the world to meet Sara. Today, you finally can." // With @samkretch, @andy_mann, and @mitty on assignment for @sealegacy. #onlyoneocean #30x30 #thelastcoralkingdom #mermaidsofauturo #timorleste

node.text: A polar bear dives below a pan of sea ice in Nunavut, Canada, its image mirrored against the water surface. One impact of climate change is a continuing loss of sea ice in the polar regions. Without a platform on which to forage seals, polar bears like this large male must resort to advanced underwater hunting techniques not available to younger, less-experienced bears. I am always fascinated at how the moments I've captured take on lives of their own, and 'Polar Reflections' has become one of my most well-known and popular photographs. // To inquire about this piece or view my entire fine art catalog, please visit the link in my bio. #FineArt #LimitedEdition #LimitedEditionPrint #Bear #PolarBear #Nunavut #Canada #Arctic #Reflection #SeaIce #PolarRegions #ClimateChange #Conservation #LifeOfItsOwn

node.text: I rarely had the opportunity to learn water sports in my youth (given most of the water was ice where I grew up), so it was a true pleasure when @NatGeo sent me to photograph Hawaii's legendary surfing community in 2013. When you can't be on the board, chasing the likes of @KalooneyTunes (pictured here), @ZekeLau, @Kala_DaCaptain, @BrianKeaulana, @KellySlater, @HealeyWaterDrops, and others with your lens as they effortlessly soar along the famous waves of #Makaha and #Pipeline is the next best thing. Our Hawaiian hosts took us in, showed us the ropes, kept us safe, and helped us return home from a dream assignment with images like 'Pipeline Poetry' that allowed us to tell their story best. // To inquire about this piece or view my entire fine art catalog, please visit the link in my bio. #FineArt #LimitedEdition #LimitedEditionPrint #Surf #Surfing #Surfers #Oahu #Hawaii #Waves #Legendary #Gratitude #Mahalo

node.text: I have spent months planning expeditions in painstaking detail, but many of my favorite encounters have popped up entirely unexpectedly. I find it is impossible to predict the next unique moment with a wild animal, and while being prepared is always a good idea, being ready is even better – ready to react, steady my hands, and release the shutter. This polar bear, seen 'Emerging' from the icy Arctic ocean in Canada's Nunavut, caught me by surprise, but he is now a proud member of my limited edition catalog because I was ready when he did. // To inquire about this piece or view my entire fine art catalog, please visit the link in my bio. #FineArt #LimitedEdition #LimitedEditionPrint #Bear #PolarBear #Nunavut #Canada #Arctic #Unexpected #Encounters #UniqueMoments #BePrepared #BeReady

node.text: #LimitedEditionPrint // An 'Orca Ballet' is the only way to describe the incredible display I witnessed below the surface of a cold fjord in northern Norway. A pod of these sophisticated apex predators weaved gracefully through the water, expertly corralling a great school of herring before plunging into its heart to stun and then feast on their prey. The continental shelf off the coast here is very narrow, stretching out anywhere between a handful of miles to as many as twenty-five before suddenly dropping off, the depth of the sea rapidly plunging from hundreds of yards to thousands. Nutrient-rich water from the deep Atlantic flows up towards the sunlight and blossoms outward, sustaining a diverse marine ecosystem on which many species  have long depended. // To inquire about this piece or view my entire fine art catalog, please visit the link in my bio. #FineArt #LimitedEdition #Orca #Herring #Lofoton #Norway #Grace #Beauty #Ballet #Conservation

node.text: ⁠#LimitedEditionPrint // As I did my best to blend in with the endless frosted tundra of Canada's Nunavut, I considered the irony that my experiences with wildlife generally begin with an attempt to hide from each other. Thanks to its flawlessly white winter coat, this 'Arctic Ghost' stayed hidden longer than most. If I am lucky, there is a moment during an encounter where I briefly establish trust and find myself connecting with an individual across a hundred million years of evolutionary differences. I released the shutter to capture an image on this occasion, but more often than not, I just sit perfectly still and enjoy the moment. // To inquire about this piece or view my entire fine art catalog, please visit the link in my bio. #FineArt #LimitedEdition #Fox #ArcticFox #Arctic #Nunavut #Canada #Snow #Ice #WhiteOnWhite #Camouflage

node.text: ⁠#LimitedEditionPrint // A large but very skinny male polar bear searches for seals along the fractured sea-ice edge in Franz Josef Land, Russia. Thriving in the planet's harshest environments is no easy feat, and polar bears must eat as much as possible during the ever-shrinking sea ice season to survive. I generally try only to imply a narrative with my photography – I believe it is important for viewers to extract the story for themselves. In the case of 'Fractured,' however, I felt a blunt approach might be more effective at inspiring a course-correction of our priorities. // To inquire about this piece or view my entire fine art catalog, please visit the link in my bio. #FineArt #LimitedEdition #Bear #PolarBear #FranzJosefLand #Russia #Ice #Hunting #Photography #Storytelling #Narrative #Conservation #CourseCorrect⁠ion

node.text: @JimmyChin's photography takes me on a journey to places few have ever visited. No one else out there is capable of capturing such beauty while hanging by a thread from a towering rock face or skiing down the legendary slopes of Mount Everest, and I am excited to finally have all of his most iconic images from twenty years of expeditions to every continent on the planet compiled in one volume. #ThereAndBack will be available on November 16th, but you can pre-order a copy today by visiting the link in my bio. It is a privilege to call one of the world's most gifted photographers a true friend – I can't wait to get lost in the poetry he has unearthed at the most extreme corners of our planet. #Book #PreOrder #Photographer #Gifted #Friend #Gratitude

node.text: On World Nature Conservation Day, I like to remember that future generations of all species are depending on us to protect the planet we share, not just our own. This encounter with a mother humpback and her calf in the warm waters of Tonga will go down as one of the most memorable of my entire career. Last week, a brief moment filmed just minutes after this photograph was taken surpassed 100 million views on @NatGeo, making it one of the most widely seen pieces of content I have ever captured. It gives me great hope to know that so many of you feel the same joy and curiosity I do when stealing a glimpse into the intimate lives of our wild cousins. I am optimistic that these shared experiences will help unite us in the name of conservation. To see the image of this little family that made it into my limited edition catalog, please visit the link in my bio. Shot on @SonyAlpha under Special Interaction Permit (Regulation 13) from the Ministry of Tonga. #SonyAlpha #SonyArtisan #BeAlpha #FineArt #LimitedEdition #Whale #Humpback #HumpbackWhale #Tonga #Diving #Underwater #Mother #Calf #Baby #Wildlife #Conservation #Gratitude

node.text: A dear friend of mine, @AmiVitale, has recently completed a gorgeous film titled 'Shaba' – the story of a young elephant rescued by the Reteti Elephant Sanctuary staff after poachers shot and killed her mother. I had the opportunity to see these iconic animals in the wild for the first time when I visited Kenya in 2017, and I returned home with a new respect for the organizations working overtime to save them from poachers and other serious threats. I invite you to visit the link in my bio and watch 'Shaba' on-demand before August 31st – tickets are by donation, and all proceeds benefit the elephants at @R.E.S.C.U.E, Africa's first indigenous-owned and operated elephant sanctuary, by funding the purchase of milk, blankets, medicines, and more. It is an incredible initiative led by a passionate group of conservationists, and I am proud to offer my support. Video by @AmiVitale. With @SararaFoundation, @ConservationOrg, @KenyaWildlifeService, @NRT_Kenya, and @Tusk_Org. #ShabaFilm #Shaba #RetetiElephantSanctuary #Elephants #Kenya #Africa #SaveElephants #StopPoaching

node.text: I am very pleased to announce that I am one of a hundred hand-selected artists, activists, journalists, scientists, and thought-leaders who have partnered with Facebook to be part of Bulletin – a brand new platform for long-form content. It has always been challenging to relate my experiences as a photographer, filmmaker, and conservationist within an Instagram caption. I am excited to finally have a place where I can share every detail of my favorite moments from the field, the philosophy behind my fine art, lessons I have learned from a lifetime in the company of wild animals, and more. My first article is the story behind the exact moment I decided what to do with my life, and it is live right now. Please visit the link in my bio to read it for yourself and subscribe to my feed, where I will be sharing many more stories and insights over the coming weeks and months. #Orca #Lofoton #Norway #Stories #Storytelling #Facebook #Bulletin #Platform #Launch #Welcome #Subscribe #Gratitude
